    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The application is designed as a single-page, vertical-scrolling portfolio with a sticky top navigation for quick access to key sections. The structure flows from a high-level summary to specific, detailed evidence: Summary -> Skills (visualized) -> Experience (timeline) -> Projects (interactive cards). This hierarchy allows recruiters to get a quick overview and then dive deeper into the areas that interest them most. The interactive elements (charts, expandable cards) are chosen to present dense information in a digestible format without overwhelming the user, promoting exploration over static reading. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Professional Summary: (Goal: Inform) -> Standard text block for immediate context.
        - Technical Skills: (Goal: Organize/Compare) -> Donut Chart (Chart.js) and styled cards. Interaction: Visual grouping and a chart to quickly show the breadth of skills in different areas. Justification: More engaging and scannable than a long bulleted list.
        - Experience: (Goal: Show Change/Inform) -> Vertical Timeline (HTML/CSS/JS). Interaction: Clicking on a job title reveals details. Justification: Visually represents career progression and chronology effectively.
        - Projects: (Goal: Organize/Inform) -> Card Grid (HTML/CSS/JS). Interaction: Expandable cards to show more details on click. Justification: Keeps the initial layout clean and allows users to explore projects of interest without leaving the page.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
